lso draws compelling comparisons between embodiment as performed in the work of these three artists and in the sit-ins and other nonviolent protests of the era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPerformance artzUnited Statesy20th century. 0aPerformance art. 0aPerformance artistsxCriticism, interpretation, etc.zUnited States. 0aPerformance artistszUnited Statesy20th century. 7aART / Performance.2bisacsh1 aAcconci, Vito, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRainer, Yvonne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneemann, Carolee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106677140 cprintz978030021797140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022043840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300220438423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300220438/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY